719018f.title: Manhattan: Coenties Slip - Water Street
719018f.text:
Coenties Slip, north side, west from Water (right) to Pearl (left) Streets, showing the South Ferrv Division of the 2nd & 3rd Avenues Elevated Lines making an "S" turn on the Slip; the train (on the left) being South Ferry bound, after coming out of Pearl Street. No. 1 is an enlargement by the photographer; No. 2 being a cop of the original
negative by the N.Y.P.L.
About 1936.
Gift of Dr. Michael Wishengrad A.N.P.S.
719018f.folder: Coenties Slip & Water Street, Manhattan, NY

719019f-b.title: Manhattan: Coenties Slip - Water Street
719019f-b.text:
Coenties Slip, north side, east from and including Water, to and including Front Streets, showing a general view northward, from No. 115 Broad Street, at the S.E. corner of Front Street, with a portion of the Second and Third Ave. Elevated in the foreground. Also shown is Front Street, east side, north from but not including
Coenties Slip, to and including Wall Street.
November 2, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
The same, from a different angle.
October 9, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
